WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.280
Chapter 15 of Proverbs. King James Version. This LibriVox recording is in the Public Domain.

00:07.440 --> 00:09.040
Recording by Michael Packard.

00:10.840 --> 00:15.820
A soft answer turneth away wrath, But grievous words stir up anger.

00:16.560 --> 00:22.620
The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright, But the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.

00:23.140 --> 00:27.220
The eyes of the Lord are in every place, Beholding the evil and the good.

00:27.220 --> 00:34.200
A wholesome tongue is a tree of life, But perverseness therein is a breach in the spirit.

00:34.900 --> 00:40.640
A fool despiseth his father's instruction, But he that regardeth reproof is prudent.

00:41.120 --> 00:46.340
In the house of the righteous is much treasure, But in the revenues of the wicked is trouble.

00:47.200 --> 00:52.040
The lips of the wise disperse knowledge, But the heart of the foolish doeth not so.

00:52.040 --> 00:58.720
The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the Lord, But the prayer of the upright is his delight.

01:00.380 --> 01:07.200
The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the Lord, But he loveth him that followeth after righteousness.

01:08.060 --> 01:13.940
Correction is grievous unto him that forsaketh the way, And he that hateth reproof shall die.

01:14.580 --> 01:19.680
Hell and destruction are before the Lord, How much more than the hearts of the children of men.

01:19.680 --> 01:25.760
A scornor loveth not one that reprooveth him, Neither will he go unto the wise.

01:26.660 --> 01:33.000
A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance, But by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.

01:33.740 --> 01:40.720
The heart of him that hath understanding seeketh knowledge, But the mouth of fools feedeth on foolishness.

01:41.040 --> 01:46.940
All the days of the afflicted are evil, But he that is of a merry heart hath a continual feast.

01:46.940 --> 01:53.280
Better is little with the fear of the Lord Than great treasure and trouble therewith.

01:53.980 --> 02:00.280
Better is a dinner of herbs where love is Than a stalled ox and hatred therewith.

02:01.700 --> 02:09.200
A wrathful man stirth up strife, But he that is slow to anger appeaseth strife.

02:09.680 --> 02:16.480
The way of the slothful man is as an hedge of thorns, But the way of the righteous is made plain.

02:17.640 --> 02:23.800
A wise son maketh a glad father, But a foolish man despiseth his mother.

02:24.800 --> 02:31.780
Folly is joy to him that is destitute of wisdom, But a man of understanding walketh uprightly.

02:32.880 --> 02:39.240
Without counsel purposes are disappointed, But in the multitude of counsellors they are established.

02:40.280 --> 02:49.420
A man hath joy by the answer of his mouth, And a word spoken in due season. How good is it!

02:50.440 --> 02:55.240
The way of life is above to the wise, That he may depart from hell beneath.

02:56.280 --> 03:01.540
The Lord will destroy the house of the proud, But he will establish the border of the widow.

03:01.540 --> 03:09.480
The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the Lord, But the words of the pure are pleasant words.

03:10.260 --> 03:17.420
He that is greedy of gain troubleth his own house, But he that hateth gifts shall live.

03:19.060 --> 03:25.100
The heart of the righteous studieth to answer, But the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.

03:25.100 --> 03:31.360
The Lord is far from the wicked, But he heareth the prayer of the righteous.

03:32.560 --> 03:38.580
The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart, And a good report maketh the bones fat.

03:40.000 --> 03:43.860
The ear that heareth the reproof of life abideth among the wise.

03:45.380 --> 03:52.060
He that refuseth instruction despiseth his own soul, But he that heareth reproof geteth understanding.

03:52.060 --> 03:59.560
The fear of the Lord is the instruction of wisdom, And before honor is humility.

